onLineSrc.orDesc: Click on the "Download this layer" link to access all digital parcels.

M239TaxPar represents a version of digital municipal parcels for the community of Plymouth,MA that is considered ‘level 3’ compliant per the specifications outlined in the MassGIS Standard for Digital Parcel Files. Its features can be linked in a GIS or database environment to a set of standardized assessing attributes in the table M239Assess by using the unique identifying values in the LOC_ID field. This data is also intended to be used in conjunction with associated (and optional) features in the ancillary data layers M239OthLeg and M239Misc. As one of the data sets identified by Massachusetts’ Strategic Plan for Spatial Data Infrastructure (http://www.mass.gov/mgis/stratplan.html), this data enters the public domain as a valuable resource for mapping, planning, and analysis at all levels of government as well as the private sector.

idCitation.resTitle: Parcel data for the Town of Plymouth, MA, complying with Level 3 of MassGIS digital parcel standard.

dataIdInfo.idAbs: This dataset is a polygon representation of the parcels for the Town of Plymouth, Massachusetts. Edits to a base parcel file were made to the spatial and tabular data in order to bring the file in compliance with November 2010 MassGIS Level III Standards for Digital Parcel Files. These edits included ensuring that the parcel fabric was continuous and closed with no gaps or overlaps. Additionally, parcels were snapped to the legislatively approved MassGIS TOWNSSURVEY_ARC town boundary datalayer and compared against the 2008 30 cm MassGIS Ortho Imagery. Polygons were assigned a LOC_ID that links to the M239 Assessor table and other fields were populated where they were known and applicable. Geometry and attribute data updated April 2018. Last updated by CGIS Mapping, LLC, August 2025.

report.measDesc: This parcel layer contains discrete, non-overlapping polygons for each property. Adjacent polygons with common ownership and a single tax record have been retained in the "OthLeg" layer that accompanies this TaxPar layer, and dissolved into single parcels in this TaxPar layer. Some non-adjacent parcels may be represented by multi-part polygons where they share common ownership and a single tax record. Public right of ways exist as polygons, not null space. Linework associated with private ROWs are retained in the "OthLeg" layer. Water polygons also representing parcel boundaries have been retained in this TaxPar layer. Additional water features that are not considered parcel boundaries may have been placed in the "Misc" layer that accompanies this TaxPar layer. Easements and other similar non-fee taxable boundaries exist in the 'OthLeg" layer, not the TaxPar layer.

Required match rate for 24649 parcels: 99.0 pct Total number of parcels with "TAX" or "FEE" POLY_TYPE and NO_MATCH = "N": 24520 Of these, 24401 join to assessor list. Match rate for "FEE"/"TAX" parcels to assessor table: 99.5 pct Parcel to assessor match rate is ok. Passes QA.

Data compiled or reviewed for horizontal accuracy over the MassGIS color orthos from 2008/2009; these orthos are known to be +/- 10' horizontal; however, this data set cannot be used to reach authoritative conclusions about the horizontal accuracy of the boundaries depicted. That work requires a licensed land surveyor.

prcStep.stepDesc: Parcel polygons were adjusted to the MassGIS TOWNSURVEY_ARC polyline along boundaries with other towns.

Parcels boundaries were visually verified against base map features in the 2008/2009 30cm USGS Color Ortho Imagery. Visual inconsistencies between the parcels and imagery of greater than 3m were fixed when such changes were supported by parcel boundaries as shown in the original assessor maps.
Topology rule checks were performed to remove slivers and gaps between taxable parcels.

Tax parcel data checked against CAMA data to identify parcel data missing assessor record information. Discrepancies were addressed through consultation with individual communities and referencing assessor maps and records.

dataSource.srcDesc: Scanned copies of Cohasset's Original Assessor maps produced by Delano & Keith, Surveyors and later maintained by the Plymouth Engineering Division were used to verify the boundaries of the GIS parcels provided by the Town of Plymouth.

overview.dsoverv: This dataset is a polygon representation of the parcels for the Town of Plymouth, Massachusetts. The town's GIS Coordinator provided Coler & Colantonio, Inc with a base parcel file (spatial data) and ownership information (tabular data), which were then upgraded to the November 2010 MassGIS Level III Standards for Digital Parcel Files. These edits included ensuring that the parcel fabric was continuous and closed with no gaps or overlaps. Additionally, parcels were snapped to the legislatively approved MassGIS TOWNSSURVEY_ARC town boundary datalayer and compared against the 2008 30 cm MassGIS Ortho Imagery. Where property lines devated by more than 3m from visible features on the imagery or crossed any visible structures, georectified assessor maps were referenced in order to validate that the parcel boundaries needed to be adjusted. Polygons were assigned a LOC_ID that links to the M239 Assessor table and other fields were populated where they were known and applicable.
